cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories, as it focuses on joint modeling of language and vision for image text retrieval. It also involves machine learning techniques such as canonical correlation analysis (CCA) and kernel methods, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed methods on image retrieval benchmarks (cs.MM).
